= Prompt Architecture =

{{info}}
**Developer Reference** - Prompt-source governance for runtime, calibration, and legacy prompt surfaces. The desired operating model is UCM-managed prompt text for analysis behavior, with explicit registry entries for every current exception.

**Status as of 2026-04-29**: ClaimBoundary, source-reliability enrichment, and input-policy prompts have file/UCM-backed surfaces. Source-reliability core prompts, grounding-check legacy sections, Stage 1 inline framing, source-reliability evidence-pack helpers, and inverse-claim calibration remain intentional exceptions. The 2026-04-29 cleanup added registry documentation only; it did not change prompt wording or model behavior.

**Key Files**: ##apps/web/src/lib/prompt-surface-registry.ts##, ##apps/web/src/lib/analyzer/prompt-loader.ts##, ##apps/web/src/lib/config-storage.ts##, ##apps/web/prompts/claimboundary/manifest.json##, ##apps/web/prompts/claimboundary.prompt.md##, ##apps/web/prompts/source-reliability.prompt.md##, ##apps/web/prompts/input-policy-gate.prompt.md##
{{/info}}

----

== 1. Overview ==

FactHarbor's target prompt architecture is:

* Prompt text that affects analysis behavior should live in UCM-manageable prompt profiles.
* File-backed defaults under ##apps/web/prompts/## are the reseed source for UCM profiles.
* Runtime code should load prompt sections through ##loadPromptConfig()## / ##loadAndRenderSection()## where possible.
* Exceptions must be explicit, named, and reviewed before migration or removal.

This page describes the current implementation. It does not grant approval to change prompt wording. Prompt wording changes still require explicit human approval under the repository prompt rules.

== 2. Prompt Surface Registry ==

The prompt-surface registry is the authoritative inventory for current prompt governance classification:

{{code language="typescript"}}
apps/web/src/lib/prompt-surface-registry.ts
{{/code}}

|= Surface |= Management |= Stability |= UCM profile/source |= Notes
| ##claimboundary## | ##manifest_backed_ucm## | Runtime contract | ##claimboundary## from ##claimboundary/manifest.json## and ##claimboundary.prompt.md## | Primary ClaimBoundary pipeline prompt. Split source files assemble into one composite UCM blob/hash.
| ##source-reliability-enrichment## | ##ucm## | Runtime contract | ##source-reliability.prompt.md## | UCM-backed source reliability enrichment sections.
| ##input-policy-gate## | ##ucm## | Runtime contract | ##input-policy-gate.prompt.md## | Pre-pipeline semantic policy gate.
| ##source-reliability-core## | ##code_built## | Intentional exception | ##sr-eval-prompts.ts## | Core SR evaluation/refinement prompts are still TypeScript builders.
| ##grounding-check-legacy## | ##db_only_legacy## | Intentional exception | DB-only ##orchestrated## profile | Grounding checks load two sections from the removed Orchestrated profile. Do not re-add an ##orchestrated## prompt file.
| ##claimboundary-pass2-inline-framing## | ##inline_code## | Intentional exception | ##claim-extraction-stage.ts## | Stage 1 Pass 2 appends fact-check framing and retry/language directives around UCM prompt sections.
| ##source-reliability-evidence-pack-inline## | ##inline_code## | Intentional exception | ##sr-eval-evidence-pack.ts## | SR evidence-pack language detection and search-term translation helpers build model-facing prompt text in code.
| ##inverse-claim-verification## | ##disk_only_calibration## | Intentional exception | ##text-analysis/inverse-claim-verification.prompt.md## | Calibration-only paired-job audit helper loaded directly from disk.

Registry tests lock the current surface IDs, exception list, and no-embedded-prompt-text rule.

== 3. Directory Structure ==

{{code language="none"}}
apps/web/prompts/
+-- claimboundary.prompt.md
+-- claimboundary/
|   +-- manifest.json
|   +-- frontmatter.prompt.md
|   +-- 01-stage1-understand.prompt.md
|   +-- 02-stage2-research.prompt.md
|   +-- 03-stage3-boundary.prompt.md
|   +-- 04-stage4-verdict.prompt.md
|   +-- 05-stage5-aggregation-report.prompt.md
|   +-- 06-late-research-and-calibration.prompt.md
|   +-- 07-stage1-contract-repair.prompt.md
+-- source-reliability.prompt.md
+-- input-policy-gate.prompt.md
+-- text-analysis/
|   +-- inverse-claim-verification.prompt.md
+-- promptfoo/
    +-- *.txt
{{/code}}

Important notes:

* ##claimboundary/manifest.json## defines the split-file source layout for the composite ##claimboundary## profile.
* ##claimboundary.prompt.md## remains the assembled compatibility blob used for seeding and hashing.
* ##source-reliability.prompt.md## is authoritative for SR enrichment prompt sections, not for the code-built SR core exception.
* ##text-analysis/inverse-claim-verification.prompt.md## is a calibration helper, not a general runtime text-analysis profile.
* ##promptfoo/## files are evaluation fixtures, not runtime prompt profiles.

== 4. Loading Flow ==

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    files["File-backed prompt defaults"] --> seed["Prompt reseed"]
    seed --> ucm["UCM config DB"]
    ucm --> load["loadPromptConfig(profile)"]
    load --> section["loadAndRenderSection(profile, section, variables)"]
    section --> llm["LLM call"]
    registry["Prompt surface registry"] --> review["Governance / review"]
    registry --> load
{{/mermaid}}

Runtime code should prefer the loader path for UCM-backed profiles. The registry documents where that is not yet true.

== 5. ClaimBoundary Prompt Layout ==

The ClaimBoundary prompt is the primary production pipeline prompt. Its split source manifest currently groups sections as follows:

|= Source file |= Section responsibility
| ##01-stage1-understand.prompt.md## | Stage 1 extraction, salience commitment, contract validation/repair appendices, ACS recommendation, and Gate 1 validation.
| ##02-stage2-research.prompt.md## | Query generation, relevance classification, evidence extraction, and scope normalization.
| ##03-stage3-boundary.prompt.md## | Boundary clustering.
| ##04-stage4-verdict.prompt.md## | Advocate, Challenger, Reconciliation, direction/grounding validation, repair, and citation-direction adjudication.
| ##05-stage5-aggregation-report.prompt.md## | Narrative generation, article adjudication, claim grouping, explanation quality, and Tiger score evaluation.
| ##06-late-research-and-calibration.prompt.md## | Applicability assessment, SR calibration, and seeded-evidence remapping.
| ##07-stage1-contract-repair.prompt.md## | Contract repair.

The assembled profile is loaded under the ##claimboundary## UCM profile. Runtime telemetry records prompt hash/section metadata through the existing analysis metrics paths.

== 6. Other Runtime Surfaces ==

=== 6.1 Source Reliability ===

Source reliability has a split governance state:

* ##source-reliability-enrichment## uses ##source-reliability.prompt.md## through UCM.
* ##source-reliability-core## remains code-built in ##sr-eval-prompts.ts##.

This is a known prompt-governance exception, not a model-quality decision. Migrating it would be a behavior-adjacent prompt-source change and should be reviewed separately.

=== 6.2 Input Policy Gate ===

The input policy gate uses the ##input-policy-gate## UCM profile. It is a pre-pipeline semantic policy gate and should remain UCM-backed because its text directly affects analysis admission behavior.

=== 6.3 Grounding Check Legacy Profile ===

Grounding checks still load ##GROUNDING_KEY_TERMS_BATCH_USER## and ##GROUNDING_ADJUDICATION_BATCH_USER## from the DB-only legacy ##orchestrated## profile. The Orchestrated pipeline was removed, so this is an intentional legacy exception. Do not recreate an ##orchestrated## prompt file merely to satisfy a directory convention.

=== 6.4 Inverse Claim Verification ===

The inverse-claim verification prompt is a paired-job audit/calibration helper loaded from disk. It is not part of the production analysis runtime path. The long-term decision is either to make it a real prompt profile or keep it explicitly calibration-only.

=== 6.5 Inline Prompt Fragments ===

Two active prompt surfaces still include model-facing text directly in code:

* Stage 1 Pass 2 inline fact-check framing and retry/language directives in ##claim-extraction-stage.ts##.
* Source-reliability evidence-pack language detection and search-term translation helpers in ##sr-eval-evidence-pack.ts##.

These are registered as intentional exceptions so future prompt-governance work can migrate or explicitly retain them with review. This page does not approve changing their wording.

== 7. Governance Rules ==

* Do not introduce new inline prompt text for analysis behavior.
* Do not change prompt wording as part of governance cleanup unless explicitly approved.
* Add new prompt surfaces to ##prompt-surface-registry.ts## with management type, stability class, owner paths, source paths, and exception rationale.
* Reseed UCM-backed prompt profiles after approved prompt-source changes.
* Keep generated summaries and observability metadata free of raw prompt text.
* Treat DB-only, code-built, or inline-code prompt surfaces as reviewable exceptions, not as normal architecture.

== 8. Adding or Migrating a Prompt Surface ==

1. Decide whether the surface affects production analysis, calibration tooling, or tests only.
1. For production analysis behavior, add a file-backed UCM prompt profile or section.
1. Register the surface in ##prompt-surface-registry.ts##.
1. Add or update focused tests that lock the profile/section ownership and exception status.
1. Reseed the prompt profile only after the source change is committed or otherwise traceable.
1. Run the relevant focused tests and ##npm -w apps/web run build##.

== 9. Changelog ==

=== 2026-04-29: Prompt Surface Registry ===

Added a source-level prompt-surface registry and refreshed this page to distinguish UCM-backed runtime prompt surfaces from intentional exceptions. No prompt wording or model behavior changed.

=== 2026-04: ClaimBoundary Split Source Layout ===

The ClaimBoundary prompt source was split into manifest-backed stage files while preserving one composite UCM profile and prompt hash.

=== 2026-02: Prompt Externalization to UCM ===

Runtime prompt loading moved toward UCM-backed ##.prompt.md## profiles. Later architecture work narrowed the old "all prompts are UCM" statement by identifying current exceptions.

